 href=\"https://github.com/UnionInternationalCheminsdeFer/OSDM\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">10</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":10,\"repo\":\"UnionInternationalCheminsdeFer/OSDM\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Aims to substantially simplify the booking process for customers of rail trips and to lower complexity and distribution costs for distributors and railway carriers. Contains a specification of an offline model and on-line API. Maintained by the <a href=\"https://github.com/UnionInternationalCheminsdeFer\">International Union of Railways (UIC)</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:34:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.allianceforparkingdatastandards.org/\">Alliance for Parking Data Standards (APDS)</a> - Formed by the <a href=\"https://www.parking.org/\">International Parking Institute (IPI)</a>, the <a href=\"http://www.britishparking.co.uk/\">British Parking Association (BPA)</a>, and the <a href=\"http://www.europeanparking.eu/\">European Parking Association (EPA)</a>, APDS is a not-for-profit organization with the mission to develop, promote, manage, and maintain a uniform global standard that will allow organizations to share parking data across platforms worldwide.  APDS Version 1.0 documents are <a href=\"https://www.allianceforparkingdatastandards.org/resources\">here</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/curblr/curblr-spec\">CurbLR</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/curblr/curblr-spec\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">53</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":53,\"repo\":\"curblr/curblr-spec\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A specification for curb regulations.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/osplanning-data-standards/dyno-demand\">Dyno-Demand</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/osplanning-data-standards/dyno-demand\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1,\"repo\":\"osplanning-data-standards/dyno-demand\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A GTFS-based travel demand data format focusing on individual passenger <em>demand</em> suitable for dynamic network modeling developed by San Francisco County Transportation Authority, LMZ LLC, and UrbanLabs LLC.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/osplanning-data-standards/dyno-path\">Dyno-Path</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/osplanning-data-standards/dyno-path\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1,\"repo\":\"osplanning-data-standards/dyno-path\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - (Under development - see <a href=\"https://github.com/osplanning-data-standards/GTFS-PLUS/pull/52#issuecomment-331231000\">this post</a>) Data for individual passenger <em>trajectories</em>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/MobilityData/gtfs-flex\">GTFS-flex</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/MobilityData/gtfs-flex\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">67</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":67,\"repo\":\"MobilityData/gtfs-flex\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A data format that models flexible public transportation services as an extension to GTFS.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ODOT-PTS/GTFS-ride\">GTFS-ride</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ODOT-PTS/GTFS-ride\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">40</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":40,\"repo\":\"ODOT-PTS/GTFS-ride\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An open, fixed-route transit ridership data standard developed through a partnership between the Oregon Department of Transportation and Oregon State University.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/zephyr-data-specs/GMNS\">General Modeling Network Specification (GMNS)</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/zephyr-data-specs/GMNS\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">41</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":41,\"repo\":\"zephyr-data-specs/GMNS\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A format for sharing routable road network files designed to be used in multi-modal static and dynamic transportation planning and operations models. Volpe/FHWA partnership with Zephyr Foundation.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://zephyrtransport.org/trb17projects/7-general-travel-network-specification/\">General Travel Network Specification</a> - A planned data specification for sharing travel demand model networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vta/Managed-and-Tolled-Lanes-Feed-Specification\">Managed and Tolled Lanes Feed Specification (MTLFS)</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vta/Managed-and-Tolled-Lanes-Feed-Specification\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":8,\"repo\":\"vta/Managed-and-Tolled-Lanes-Feed-Specification\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Proposal for a schema that comprise the Managed and Tolled Lanes Tolling Feed Specification (MTLFS) and defines the fields used in all of those files developed by <a href=\"http://www.vta.org/\">Santa Clara Valley Transportation Authority</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/openmobilityfoundation/mobility-data-specification\">Mobility Data Specification (MDS)</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/openmobilityfoundation/mobility-data-specification\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">510</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":510,\"repo\":\"openmobilityfoundation/mobility-data-specification\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A format to implement realtime data sharing, measurement and regulation for municipalities and mobility as a service providers. It is meant to ensure that governments have the ability to enforce, evaluate and manage providers. Maintained by the <a href=\"https://www.openmobilityfoundation.org/\">Open Mobility Foundation</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://netex-cen.eu/\">NeTex</a> - A general purpose XML format designed for the exchange of complex static transport data among distributed systems managed by the <a href=\"https://www.cen.eu/work/ENdev/how/Pages/default.aspx\">CEN standards process</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://articles.sae.org/15799/\">SAE Shared and Digital Mobility Committee</a> - Appears to be working on a data standard for car share and transportation network companies (TNCs) / rideshare.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://apps.trb.org/cmsfeed/TRBNetProjectDisplay.asp?ProjectID=4120\">TCRP G-16 Development of Transactional Data Specifications for Demand-Responsive Transportation (In progress)</a> - The objective of this research is to develop technical specifications for transactional data for entities involved in the provision of demand-responsive transportation.  Expected completion date is late 2018.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h3>Other multimodal data formats</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/tidesproject\">TIDES project</a> -  Transit ITS Data Exchange Specification (TIDES) is a proposed effort to create standard data structures, APIs, and data management tools for historical transit ITS data including AVL, APC and AFC Data.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:27:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"aliesbelik/awesome-jmeter","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2><h3>Editors</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jmeter-plugins.org/editor/\">BlocklyJMX Editor</a> - A web-based viewer and editor for JMeter test plan files (part of <a href=\"#plugins\">JMeter Plugins</a> project).</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:26:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"aliesbelik/awesome-jmeter","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2><h3>Editors</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/QAInsights/JEval\">JEval</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/QAInsights/JEval\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">21</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":21,\"repo\":\"QAInsights/JEval\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A Python-based utility which evaluates JMeter test plan and provides recommendations and best practices by analyzing each element.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-07T19:26:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"bcoe/awesome-cross-platform-nodejs","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ehmicky/cross-platform-terminal-characters\">Cross-platform terminal characters</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ehmicky/cross-platform-terminal-characters\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">168</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":168,\"repo\":\"ehmicky/cross-platform-terminal-characters\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_IT